<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_45c2b891-eea6-41a4-bb7d-0d98304d7d19" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>8.2.1</sptc><title id="_e768bdd1-bf46-4bac-9a31-049d303824e0">Application</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_33c7b726-7150-4731-b992-e5302297d2d7" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_8b751e35-96d5-4ceb-9e96-8fd6a526b0de">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4209_0.13.0.xml#_45f9cb17-0021-4b49-ab59-158110346fed" id="_16904a76-ac68-43a2-b2e8-238f067fcb2c" scope="local" type="part">Part 8.2</xref> applies subject to the limitations set out in <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1811#_45a3e80c-a551-4683-8f03-7f17dc9ed31a" id="_cabddf83-c3fc-486c-a0d1-181197e63ad5" publishing-id="vol2" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">H1D8(1)</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1811#_c703fd74-5ef5-435c-85aa-3d9da82ed6c4" id="_33f26da4-4ff8-46fc-ade6-e2ae7a64a915" publishing-id="vol2" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">(2)</xref>.</p></subclause><callout id="_6f937e1e-c4cc-4026-ad7f-03a776129d19"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>This Part does not cover the installation of assemblies that are internal or revolving doors, fixed louvres, skylights, rooflights and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_e53ea792-3d11-45b5-9144-85e2a1c966a1" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> not installed in the vertical plane, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_9868d878-90ab-4aee-8466-34fdeb76f608" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> in greenhouses or horticultural buildings or frameless sliding doors.</p><p>The term ‘one piece framing’ in <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/1811#_45a3e80c-a551-4683-8f03-7f17dc9ed31a" id="_ae505442-8f9d-41d9-b27c-1415a9f0e235" publishing-id="vol2" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">H1D8(1)(a)(iv)</xref> generally refers to glazing installed in the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_c3484be7-e6c7-423d-aec1-8f45065b30e0" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> of a building where the external fabric is forming the frame.</p></callout></clause>